  "prompt": "Is variance another word for standard deviation?",
  "response": "No, variance and standard deviation are related but different statistical measures:\n\n1. Variance:\n- Measures the average squared deviation from the mean\n- Calculated by taking the average of squared differences from the mean\n- Expressed in squared units of the original data\n\n2. Standard Deviation:\n- The square root of variance\n- Measures the average distance between data points and the mean\n- Expressed in the same units as the original data\n- Provides a more intuitive measure of spread\n\nSo while they are closely related, they are not the same thing. Standard deviation is derived from variance by taking its square root.",
